==English==
===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[gyrdan]]'' (to put a belt around, to put a girdle around).

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)d|-ɜː(r)d]]

====Verb====
{{irregverb|'''to gird'''|'''[[girds]]'''|'''[[girded]] '''or''' [[girt]]'''|'''[[girded]] '''or''' [[girt]]'''|'''[[girding]]'''}}
#''(transitive)'' To [[bind]] with a [[flexible]] [[rope]] or [[cord]], much like a belt.
#:''The fasces were '''girt''' about with twine in bundles large.''
#:''The lady '''girt''' herself with silver chain, from which she hung a golden shear.''
